2 Sec. 5. K.S.A. 25-101b is hereby amended to read as follows: 25-
3 101b. (a) At the general election held in 1978 and each four (4) years
4 thereafter, there shall be elected a treasurer for the state of Kansas, whose
5 term of office shall be four (4) years beginning on the second Monday in
6 January next succeeding such treasurer's election. In case of a vacancy in
7 such office, within two three calendar days after receiving a concurrent
8 resolution adopted pursuant to section 4, and amendments thereto, or a
9 report submitted pursuant to section 3, and amendments thereto, the
10 governor shall appoint some suitable person one of the three persons
11 recommended as candidates in such concurrent resolution or report to
12 serve for the unexpired term and until a successor is elected and qualified.
13 No person shall be appointed pursuant to this section unless such person
14 is a resident of this state and shall have been registered with the same
15 political party for the immediately preceding six years as that of the state
16 treasurer elected at the immediately preceding election for such office. If
17 the state treasurer elected at the immediately preceding election for such
18 office was not registered with any political party, then any suitable person
19 who is a resident of this state may be appointed pursuant to sections 2
20 through 4, and amendments thereto.
21 (b) No person appointed pursuant to subsection (a) shall take office
22 unless such appointment is certified by the secretary of state. The
23 secretary shall not certify any person as being appointed to fill a vacancy
24 in the office of treasurer for the state of Kansas unless such person is
25 appointed in accordance with this section.
